PART 3 : ENVIRONMENT
Operating System
The project was developed and run on Windows (office laptop) and possibly Linux (server).

No OS‑specific code is used; all scripts are OS‑agnostic Python 3.

Python Version
Python 3.8+ is recommended.

The code uses f‑strings, type hints, and standard library features compatible with Python 3.8 and above.

The exact version used locally is not documented, but 3.8, 3.9, or 3.10 are safe.

Conda / Virtual Environment
The team used a conda environment (typical for data science projects), but the exact environment name is not recorded.

It can be recreated with the requirements.txt below, either via conda or pip.

Recreate with conda (example):

bash
conda create -n sensor_auth python=3.9
conda activate sensor_auth
pip install -r requirements.txt
Or using venv:

bash
python -m venv sensor_auth_env
source sensor_auth_env/bin/activate   # Linux/Mac
# or sensor_auth_env\Scripts\activate on Windows
pip install -r requirements.txt
