CUDA / GPU
No GPU is used or required. All machine learning (OCSVM, Random Forest, XGBoost) runs on CPU.

The dataset is small enough (a few thousand samples, ~500 features) that training is fast on a modern CPU.

If XGBoost detects a GPU, it might use it by default; the scripts set n_jobs=-1 for parallel CPU usage.

GPU Details
Not applicable.

Installation Commands (full setup)
Assuming a fresh Python 3.9 environment:

bash
# Create and activate environment
conda create -n sensor_auth python=3.9 -y
conda activate sensor_auth

# Install all dependencies
pip install numpy pandas scikit-learn xgboost boruta shap scipy matplotlib seaborn PyWavelets dtw joblib

# Verify imports
python -c "import numpy, pandas, sklearn, xgboost, boruta, shap, scipy, matplotlib, seaborn, pywt, dtw, joblib; print('All imports successful')"
If any package fails, install it separately with conda when possible.

Additional Notes
The dtw package used is the dtw library (not dtw-python), installed via pip install dtw.

For shap, version 0.40+ is recommended because it includes the TreeExplainer used in Phase 2A.

The boruta package must be version ≥0.3, which supports BorutaPy with n_estimators='auto'.

No specific CUDA or GPU drivers are needed.

